<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<ScrollView xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    android:paddingBottom="@dimen/activity_vertical_margin"
    android:paddingLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
    android:paddingRight="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
    android:paddingTop="@dimen/activity_vertical_margin"
    tools:context="com.example.pc.vtuecesyllabus.Sem6cbcscnlabActivity"
    android:fillViewport="false">
    <RelativeLayout
        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content">

        <TextView
            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:text="       Electronics and Communication Eng.:Semester-6"
            android:id="@+id/heading"
            android:layout_alignParentRight="true"
            android:layout_alignParentEnd="true"
            android:layout_alignParentTop="true"
            android:layout_alignParentLeft="true"
            android:layout_alignParentStart="true"
            android:background="#cd4a4de1"
            android:textColor="#ffffff" />
        <View
            android:layout_width="fill_parent"
            android:layout_height="1dp"
            android:background="#0d0c0c"
            android:layout_below="@+id/heading"
            android:id="@+id/headinglin" />


        <TextView
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="match_parent"
            android:text="COMPUTER NETWORKS LABORATORY"

            android:id="@+id/text1"
            android:textAlignment="center"
            android:textStyle="bold"
            android:layout_below="@+id/headinglin"
            android:textSize="25dp" />

        <TableLayout
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="match_parent"
            android:layout_below="@+id/text1"
            android:id="@+id/table">

            <TableRow
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="match_parent">

                <TextView
                    android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                    android:text="Sub Code:15ECL68"
                    android:id="@+id/text2"
                    android:textSize="18dp"
                    android:layout_column="0" />

            </TableRow>

            <TableRow
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="match_parent">

                <TextView
                    android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                    android:text="Credits : 02"
                    android:textSize="18dp"
                    android:id="@+id/text3"
                    android:layout_column="0" />
            </TableRow>


            <TableRow
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="match_parent">

                <TextView
                    android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                    android:text="Total No. of Lecture Hours/Week : 01Hr Tutorial(Instructions)+02 Hours Laboratory."
                    android:id="@+id/text5"
                    android:textSize="18dp"
                    android:layout_column="0" />
            </TableRow>

            <TableRow
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="match_parent">

                <TextView
                    android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                    android:text="IA Marks : 20"
                    android:id="@+id/text"
                    android:textSize="18dp"
                    android:layout_column="0" />
            </TableRow>
            <TableRow
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="match_parent">

                <TextView
                    android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                    android:text="Exam Marks: 80"
                    android:id="@+id/text6"
                    android:textSize="18dp"
                    android:layout_column="0" />
            </TableRow>


            <TableRow
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="match_parent">

                <TextView
                    android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                    android:text="Exam Hours : 03"
                    android:id="@+id/text7"
                    android:textSize="18dp"
                    android:layout_column="0" />
            </TableRow>

            <TableRow
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="match_parent">

            </TableRow>

            <TableRow
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="match_parent">

            </TableRow>

            <TableRow
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="match_parent"></TableRow>

            <TableRow
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="match_parent">

                <TextView
                    android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                    android:text="    "
                    android:id="@+id/text8"
                    android:layout_column="0" />
            </TableRow>

            <TableRow
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="match_parent">

                <TextView
                    android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                    android:text="Course Objectives:"
                    android:id="@+id/text9"
                    android:textSize="21dp"
                    android:textStyle="bold"

                    android:layout_column="0" />
            </TableRow>
        </TableLayout>

        <TextView
            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:text="  This laboratory course enables students to:\n• Choose suitable tools to model a network and understand the protocols at various OSI reference levels.\n• Design a suitable network and simulate using a Network simulator tool.\n• Simulate the networking concepts and protocols using C/C++ programming.\n• Model the networks for different configurations and analyze the results."
            android:layout_below="@+id/table"
            android:textSize="15dp"
            android:id="@+id/text10" />

        <TextView
            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:text="Laboratory Experiments:"
            android:textAlignment="center"
            android:layout_marginTop="3dp"
            android:textSize="19dp"
            android:textStyle="bold"
            android:layout_below="@+id/text10"

            android:id="@+id/text11" />

        <TextView
            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:text="PART-A: Simulation experiments using  NS2/ NS3/ OPNET/ NCTUNS/ NetSim/QualNet/ Packet Tracer or any other equivalent tool "
            android:layout_marginTop="2dp"
            android:textSize="16dp"
            android:textStyle="bold"
            android:layout_below="@+id/text11"

            android:id="@+id/text12" />
        <TextView
            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:text="1. Implement a point to pint network with four nodes and duplex links between them. Analyze the network performance by setting the queue size and varying the bandwidth.\n2. Implement a four node point to point network with links n0-n2, n1-n2 and n2-n3. Apply TCP agent between n0-n3 and UDP between n1-n3. Apply relevant applications over TCP and UDP agents changing the parameter and determine the number of packets sent by TCP/UDP.\n3. Implement Ethernet LAN using n (6-10) nodes. Compare the throughput by changing the error rate and data rate.\n4. Implement Ethernet LAN using n nodes and assign multiple traffic to the nodes and obtain congestion window for different sources/ destinations.\n5. Implement ESS with transmission nodes in Wireless LAN and obtain the performance parameters.\n6. Implementation of Link state routing algorithm."
            android:layout_marginTop="2dp"
            android:textSize="15dp"
            android:layout_below="@+id/text12"

            android:id="@+id/text13" />


        <TextView
            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:text="PART-B: Implement the following in C/C++ "
            android:layout_marginTop="11dp"
            android:textSize="16dp"
            android:textStyle="bold"
            android:layout_below="@+id/text13"
            android:id="@+id/text14" />
        <TextView
            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:text="1. Write a program for a HLDC frame to perform the following.\n   i) Bit stuffing\n   ii) Character stuffing.\n2. Write a program for distance vector algorithm to find suitable path for transmission.\n3. Implement Dijkstra’s algorithm to compute the shortest routing path.\n4. For the given data, use CRC-CCITT polynomial to obtain CRC code. Verify the program for the cases\n     a. Without error\n     b. With error\n5. Implementation of Stop and Wait Protocol and Sliding Window Protocol\n6. Write a program for congestion control using leaky bucket algorithm.  "
            android:layout_marginTop="2dp"
            android:textSize="15dp"
            android:layout_below="@+id/text14"

            android:id="@+id/text15" />


        <TextView
            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:text="Conduct of Practical Examination:"
            android:layout_marginTop="11dp"
            android:textSize="16dp"
            android:textStyle="bold"
            android:layout_below="@+id/text15"
            android:id="@+id/text16" />
        <TextView
            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:text="• All laboratory experiments are to be included for practical examination.\n•For examination one question from software and one question from hardware or only one hardware experiments based on the complexity to be set.\n• Students are allowed to pick one experiment from the lot.\n• Strictly follow the instructions as printed on the cover page of answer script for breakup of marks.\n• Change of experiment is allowed only once and 15% Marks allotted to the procedure part to be made zero.\n

                                           ***"
            android:layout_marginTop="2dp"
            android:textSize="15dp"
            android:layout_below="@+id/text16"
            android:id="@+id/text17" />



    </RelativeLayout>
</ScrollView>
